clue: This charity traces its origins to a 7-year-old boy battling cancer who got to fulfill his dream of being a police officer

response: Make-A-Wish

clue: This Children's Hospital is named for the patron saint of hopeless causes

response: St. Jude

clue: May 28, 1961, when the newspaper story "The Forgotten Prisoners" ran, is considered the founding date of this organization

response: Amnesty International

clue: This group of diseases is paired with leukemia in the name of a society that invests in research to cure blood cancers

response: lymphoma

clue: Founded to protect places & species threatened by human development, it got its name & its giant panda logo in 1961

response: the WWF (World Wildlife Fund)

